<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFFFBFFCCFF89279BFE8D8CC3" lastPageId="108" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" type="description">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFFBFFC8FF89279BFCFD88BB" blockId="104.[94,622,1124,1763]" lastBlockId="104.[670,1199,214,1763]" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">
IDENTIFICATION: The most recent revision of the smaller species of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FE7F27B5FE7B8C85" authorityName="Leach. In B. D. Patterson and R. M. Timm" authorityYear="1821" box="[397,496,1447,1470]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FE7F27B5FE7B8C85" box="[397,496,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Artibeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FFAC27D6FF6D8CE0" box="[94,230,1476,1499]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dermanura">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FFAC27D6FF6D8CE0" box="[94,230,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Dermanura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is Handleyâ€™s (1987), whose meticulous species comparisons and key were our primary resource for identification. Additional comparative measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FDDE240EFF208F6B" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FDDE240EFDB58F08" box="[556,574,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FDBD240EFF208F6B" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FF1F242BFEE78F6B" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1987" box="[237,364,1593,1616]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FF1F242BFF748F6B" box="[237,255,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FEE0242BFEE78F6B" box="[274,364,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">gnomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from French Guiana provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFFBFFC8FF072444FF208FB0" author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and CharlesÂ­Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
were also helpful. Although both species probably occur in Surinam and may have been mixed in earlier collections, 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFFBFFC8FDC724BCFF658FD8" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Hussonâ€™s (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978) account of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FE1624DEFDE58FD8" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[484,622,1740,1763]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FE1624DEFE7D8FD8" box="[484,502,1740,1763]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FDFE24DEFDE58FD8" box="[524,622,1740,1763]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to have been based entirely upon specimens properly referred to that species. Koopman (1994) listed seven subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FD6C233DFCAA887D" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[670,801,302,326]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD6C233DFD3B887D" box="[670,688,303,326]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD4D233DFCAA887D" box="[703,801,303,326]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however all but two of these appear to represent other species (see Handley, 1987, and below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFFBFFC8FD492394FB218BF8" blockId="104.[670,1199,214,1763]" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">
Our voucher material, one of the largest series of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FCE323B6FC698880" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[785,994,420,443]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FCE323B6FC698880" box="[785,994,420,443]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Artibeus cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported from a single locality, conforms in all respects to Handleyâ€™s (1987) description of the species. Although our specimens generally fall within the range of morphometric variation previously reported in the literature, a few individuals of both sexes are slightly smaller in some dimensions than those documented from the Guianas by 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFFBFFC8FC5F209CFBD38B9E" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[941,1112,654,677]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978) and 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFFBFFC8FD2020BEFB2D8BF8" author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" box="[722,1190,684,707]" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and CharlesÂ­Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFFBFFC8FD4920DBFC938C10" blockId="104.[670,1199,214,1763]" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">
As with the larger species of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FBBE20DBFB248BDB" authorityName="Leach. In B. D. Patterson and R. M. Timm" authorityYear="1821" box="[1100,1199,713,736]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FBBE20DBFB248BDB" box="[1100,1199,713,736]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Artibeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FCEE20F5FCF48BC5" authorityName="Leach. In B. D. Patterson and R. M. Timm" authorityYear="1821" box="[796,895,743,766]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FCEE20F5FCF48BC5" box="[796,895,743,766]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Artibeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), we found that we could not always distinguish species of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FBD42116FB258A20" box="[1062,1198,772,795]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dermanura">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FBD42116FB258A20" box="[1062,1198,772,795]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Dermanura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the field. Most individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FBED2133FB0A8A03" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[1055,1153,801,824]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FBED2133FB0A8A03" box="[1055,1153,801,824]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger than most specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FBFB212DFBE88A6D" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1987" box="[1033,1123,831,854]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FBFB212DFBE88A6D" box="[1033,1123,831,854]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">gnomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(table 39), and most 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FCA6214EFC3D8A48" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[852,950,860,883]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FCA6214EFC3D8A48" box="[852,950,860,883]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have creamÂ­colored ear margins and tragus while those structures are bright yellow in most 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FC262185FBA58A95" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1987" box="[980,1070,919,942]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC262185FBA58A95" box="[980,1070,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">gnomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, we captured some individuals that we initially misidentified using these characters. Of 67 collected specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FC0121FDFBF08D3D" box="[1011,1147,1007,1030]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dermanura">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC0121FDFBF08D3D" box="[1011,1147,1007,1030]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Dermanura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 65 (97%) were correctly identified in the field; two individuals (3%) were initially identified incorrectly, both cases involving specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FD362676FCC58D40" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[708,846,1124,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD362676FD5D8D40" box="[708,726,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD1E2676FCC58D40" box="[748,846,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(one male and one female) misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FC932693FC568DA3" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1987" box="[865,989,1153,1176]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC932693FCF88DA3" box="[865,883,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC712693FC568DA3" box="[899,989,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">gnomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We had to clean the skulls of these and several other specimens that fell in the zone of size overlap between 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FD1C26CBFCF88DCB" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[750,883,1241,1264]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD1C26CBFC8B8DCB" box="[750,768,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FCE326CBFCF88DCB" box="[785,883,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FC4126CBFBBA8DCB" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1987" box="[947,1073,1241,1264]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC4126CBFC4E8DCB" box="[947,965,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC2526CBFBBA8DCB" box="[983,1073,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">gnomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see table 39) in order to determine their correct identifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFFBFFCCFD492723FE4D8D18" blockId="104.[670,1199,214,1763]" lastBlockId="108.[94,623,918,1763]" lastPageId="108" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">
We are unaware of any external characters that allow unequivocal identification of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FB75275DFCDA8CB8" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FB75275DFCDA8CB8" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">Artibeus cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FC66277EFB988CB8" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1987" box="[916,1043,1388,1411]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC66277EFC2D8CB8" box="[916,934,1388,1411]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC4B277EFB988CB8" box="[953,1043,1388,1411]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">gnomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where these taxa occur in sympatry, but the number of lower molars appears to be reliable in our Paracou sample: all individuals with two lower molars present on 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC3327F3FC7E8CC3" box="[961,1013,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">both</emphasis>
sides proved to be 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FD3327EDFCCF8F2D" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[705,836,1534,1558]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD3327EDFD588F2D" box="[705,723,1535,1558]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD1027EDFCCF8F2D" box="[738,836,1535,1558]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
upon subsequent examination, and all individuals with three lower molars on 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD37242BFD728F6B" box="[709,761,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">both</emphasis>
sides were 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FC79242BFB828F6B" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1987" box="[907,1033,1593,1616]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gnomus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC79242BFC168F6B" box="[907,925,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FC5D242BFB828F6B" box="[943,1033,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">gnomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(one individual of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFFBFFC8FD192445FCC68F55" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[747,845,1623,1646]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="104" pageNumber="104" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinereus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFFBFFC8FD192445FCC68F55" box="[747,845,1623,1646]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="104">cinereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had two lower molars on one side and three on the other). Although the number of lower molars is perhaps the best single character for distinguishing these taxa in the field, it is not very useful for nondeÂ­ structive research projects because m3 (when present) is small, translucent, and easily obscured by saliva; hence, we found it almost impossible to unambiguously determine if m3 was present in living bats.
</paragraph>
